{Essentially, not much has changed here to this day: Even today, people are seduced into focusing on material wealth, sex, and greater influence (power) instead of living their light and love. Some who couldn't resist these temptations even "walk over dead bodies." In other words, they act against the interests of others and to their detriment. Love would never do or support that! You can still observe all of these mechanisms every day in our world: whether in politics, in business, or among the many people who try to take money out of other people's pockets in a variety of ways without fair compensation. The question is, to what extent can you resist the many temptations, distractions, and confusing actions in our world. Do you measure your thoughts and actions by whether what you think, say, or do is out of love and serves love? If you serve love, you serve the light. If not, you serve the darkness. It's that simple. And yet so many people are so confused by the media and the information and sensory overload that they don't realize this.}
{Love your enemies! Love cannot suffer because it cannot attack. Therefore, the memory of love brings with it invulnerability. Your friends usually agree with you. But your 'enemies' don't; they look for your weak points and will reflect back to you everything you dislike about yourself. They will show you exactly where your fears and insecurities lie. If you listen carefully to your 'enemies,' you can recognize where you can correct yourself or work on yourself. Each of us encounters both 'allies' and 'enemies' throughout our lives. A good enemy is also your best ally because they are your best teacher. They give you a gift! If you can recognize this and are willing to love your enemies, you demonstrate your willingness to look into the darkest corners of yourself. You don't have to agree with your enemies to make peace with them. But you can learn to see things from your opponents' perspective. When love and mutual respect exist, peace arises! Not only within you, but also with others around you. Love means being able to say NO. However, unconditional love does not mean agreeing to everything. Saying NO can also be an act of love. A 'no' can be made out of love. For example, when you want to protect the other person, when it comes to destructive behavior, or when it comes to naming errors and telling the truth. Standing up for the truth is not always popular. With a NO, you risk being no longer loved or even rejected by certain people. But if a NO corresponds to your truth and your honest point of view, a 'yes' would be hypocrisy â€“ and this would serve neither yourself nor others. True love sets boundaries against everything that would harm or hinder the well-being of the soul. She does not judge, she does not fight anything or anyone, she only looks lovingly at everything that is and lovingly protects what she loves.}
{Liebe deine Feinde! Die Liebe kann nicht leiden, weil sie nicht angreifen kann. Daher bringt die Erinnerung an die Liebe Unverletzlichkeit mit sich. Deine Freunde stimmen dir in der Regel zu. Doch deine 'Feinde' tun dies nicht, sie suchen deine Schwachpunkte und werden dir alles spiegeln, was du an dir selbst nicht magst. Sie werden dir genau zeigen, wo deine Ã„ngste und Unsicherheiten liegen. Wenn du deinen 'Feinden' genau zuhÃ¶rst, kannst du erkennen, an welchen Punkten du dich selbst korrigieren oder an dir arbeiten kannst. Jeder von uns trifft im Laufe seines Lebens sowohl auf 'VerbÃ¼ndete' wie auch auf 'Gegner'. Ein guter Gegner ist gleichzeitig dein bester VerbÃ¼ndeter, denn er ist dein bester Lehrer. Er macht dir ein Geschenk! Wenn du dies erkennen kannst und bereit bist, deine Feinde zu lieben, zeigst du damit deine Bereitschaft, in die dunkelsten Winkel deines Inneren zu schauen. Du musst deinen Feinden nicht zustimmen, um mit ihnen Frieden zu schlieÃŸen. Aber du kannst lernen, die Dinge auch aus dem Blickwinkel deiner Gegner zu betrachten. {Ğ¥The Blindness of Humanity to the Wonders of the Universe: Seeing, Gratitude, and Love Modern humans are surrounded by wonders, yet paradoxically, they do not see them. We take pride in scientific discoveries, marvel at technological complexity, yet remain blind to the deepest beauty of the cosmos. We see equations but do not understand what lies behind them. We observe molecules and elementary particles but fail to grasp that they are part of a grand cosmic dance, performed with mathematical precision and sublime aesthetics. If humans truly saw the world, they would be unable to destroy it. If they realized how intricate, beautiful, and deliberately designed everything around them is, they would not pick up weapons, kill, or wage wars. Life is a miracle, and our purpose is to see, admire, be grateful, and love. The Living Mathematics of Nature Nature is perfect in its mathematical organization. Take, for example, the golden ratioâ€”a proportion found in seashells, the arrangement of leaves on stems, the structure of the human body, and even the spirals of galaxies. Why does mathematics not merely describe nature but seem to be woven into its very fabric? Could this not be a sign of intelligent design? Another example is snowflakes. Each is a sixfold symmetrical masterpiece, formed by the crystallization of water molecules. Every unique pattern results from a complex interplay of physical forces. If we see order, does it not imply the presence of an intelligence that established this order? The Metaphysical Wonders of Physics Quantum physics defies our common sense, yet we often overlook the profound metaphysical implications hidden within it. 	â€¢	A particle can exist as both a wave and a solid object at the same time. 	â€¢	An electron can be in multiple places simultaneously. 	â€¢	Quantum entanglement allows two particles to influence each other instantaneously, even across vast distances, seemingly defying the speed of light. Quantum mechanics challenges our fundamental understanding of reality. Perhaps the universe is not merely a mechanical system but something far greater. If the microscopic world is filled with mystery, why do we reject the possibility of a grander intelligence at the macroscopic level? The Secret of Life: Between Death and Resurrection Nature presents us with astonishing examples of what could be called resurrection. 	â€¢	â€œPhoenixâ€ fish. African lungfish survive droughts by burrowing into the mud and entering a state of suspended animation. Their bodies dry out completely, yet when water returnsâ€”even years laterâ€”they revive. 	â€¢	Frozen snakes and frogs. In northern regions, certain snakes and frogs freeze solid during winter. Their hearts stop beating, their blood ceases to flow. But in spring, they come back to life as if nothing happened. 	â€¢	Seeds waiting for thousands of years. Scientists have found seeds buried for millennia that still sprout when planted. We dismiss these as mere biological mechanisms, but why are we so eager to ignore the deeper significance of such phenomena? Peacock Feathers and Ultraviolet Visionâ€”Natureâ€™s Hidden Language Some of the most breathtaking natural phenomena are not only beautiful but also rooted in sophisticated physical processes. 	â€¢	Peacock feathers. Their vivid colors do not come from pigments but from the physics of light interference. Light waves bend and interact in microscopic layers of keratin, producing mesmerizing iridescence. 	â€¢	Butterflies and beetles. Many insects use the same technique to create colors that no ordinary pigment could replicate. 	â€¢	The ultraviolet world. Humans see only a limited portion of the spectrum, but bees and other creatures perceive ultraviolet patterns invisible to us. Many flowers have intricate UV markings that guide pollinators directly to their nectar, like cosmic landing strips. Nature is not only functional but artistic. We see peacocks, butterflies, flowers, and rainbows. But we do not see them as we could. Everything Moves at Unimaginable Speedsâ€”Even Your Furniture We perceive our daily environment as motionless. A table stands still, food sits on a plate, a wall does not move. Yet at the atomic level, everything is in a state of ceaseless motion. 	â€¢	Electrons orbit atomic nuclei at 2,200 km/s. If we shrank down to their scale, our furniture would appear as massive, swirling clouds of energy. 	â€¢	The Earth rotates at 1,670 km/h, races around the Sun at 107,000 km/h, and the Solar System itself moves through the Milky Way at an astonishing 828,000 km/h. Why donâ€™t we feel this? Perhaps because the universe is designed in such a way that we can focus on what truly mattersâ€”the meaning of life, the pursuit of truth. Choosing Love Over Destruction If the universe is so wonderfully designedâ€”if every phenomenon, from quantum mechanics to the iridescence of butterfly wings, carries deep meaningâ€”why do we insist on destroying this world? We are surrounded by perfection. We do not need to reinvent anything. We have water, air, plants, sunlight, and food. We have the ability to enjoy, to be grateful, to love. Life is a gift that should not be wasted on war, violence, and killing.}

Surah Al A'raf ayat 26 ÙŠÙ°Ø¨ÙÙ†ÙÙŠÙ’Ù“ Ø§Ù°Ø¯ÙÙ…Ù Ù‚ÙØ¯Ù’ Ø§ÙÙ†Ù’Ø²ÙÙ„Ù’Ù†ÙØ§ Ø¹ÙÙ„ÙÙŠÙ’ÙƒÙÙ…Ù’ Ù„ÙØ¨ÙØ§Ø³Ù‹Ø§ ÙŠÙÙ‘ÙˆÙØ§Ø±ÙÙŠÙ’ Ø³ÙÙˆÙ’Ø¡Ù°ØªÙÙƒÙÙ…Ù’ ÙˆÙØ±ÙÙŠÙ’Ø´Ù‹Ø§Û— ÙˆÙÙ„ÙØ¨ÙØ§Ø³Ù Ø§Ù„ØªÙÙ‘Ù‚Ù’ÙˆÙ°Ù‰ Ø°Ù°Ù„ÙÙƒÙ Ø®ÙÙŠÙ’Ø±ÙŒÛ— Ø°Ù°Ù„ÙÙƒÙ Ù…ÙÙ†Ù’ Ø§Ù°ÙŠÙ°ØªÙ Ø§Ù„Ù„Ù‘Ù°Ù‡Ù Ù„ÙØ¹ÙÙ„ÙÙ‘Ù‡ÙÙ…Ù’ ÙŠÙØ°ÙÙ‘ÙƒÙÙ‘Ø±ÙÙˆÙ’Ù†Ù Artinya: Wahai anak cucu Adam, sungguh Kami telah menurunkan kepadamu pakaian untuk menutupi auratmu dan bulu (sebagai bahan pakaian untuk menghias diri). (Akan tetapi,) pakaian takwa itulah yang paling baik. Yang demikian itu merupakan sebagian tanda-tanda (kekuasaan) Allah agar mereka selalu ingat. 3. Surah An-Nur ayat 31 ÙˆÙÙ‚ÙÙ„Ù’ Ù„ÙÙ‘Ù„Ù’Ù…ÙØ¤Ù’Ù…ÙÙ†Ù°ØªÙ ÙŠÙØºÙ’Ø¶ÙØ¶Ù’Ù†Ù Ù…ÙÙ†Ù’ Ø§ÙØ¨Ù’ØµÙØ§Ø±ÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ ÙˆÙÙŠÙØ­Ù’ÙÙØ¸Ù’Ù†Ù ÙÙØ±ÙÙˆÙ’Ø¬ÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ ÙˆÙÙ„ÙØ§ ÙŠÙØ¨Ù’Ø¯ÙÙŠÙ’Ù†Ù Ø²ÙÙŠÙ’Ù†ÙØªÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ø§ÙÙ„ÙÙ‘Ø§ Ù…ÙØ§ Ø¸ÙÙ‡ÙØ±Ù Ù…ÙÙ†Ù’Ù‡ÙØ§ ÙˆÙÙ„Ù’ÙŠÙØ¶Ù’Ø±ÙØ¨Ù’Ù†Ù Ø¨ÙØ®ÙÙ…ÙØ±ÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ø¹ÙÙ„Ù°Ù‰ Ø¬ÙÙŠÙÙˆÙ’Ø¨ÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘Û– ÙˆÙÙ„ÙØ§ ÙŠÙØ¨Ù’Ø¯ÙÙŠÙ’Ù†Ù Ø²ÙÙŠÙ’Ù†ÙØªÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ø§ÙÙ„ÙÙ‘Ø§ Ù„ÙØ¨ÙØ¹ÙÙˆÙ’Ù„ÙØªÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ø§ÙÙˆÙ’ Ø§Ù°Ø¨ÙØ§Û¤Ù‰ÙÙ•Ù‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ø§ÙÙˆÙ’ Ø§Ù°Ø¨ÙØ§Û¤Ø¡Ù Ø¨ÙØ¹ÙÙˆÙ’Ù„ÙØªÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ø§ÙÙˆÙ’ Ø§ÙØ¨Ù’Ù†ÙØ§Û¤Ù‰ÙÙ•Ù‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ø§ÙÙˆÙ’ Ø§ÙØ¨Ù’Ù†ÙØ§Û¤Ø¡Ù Ø¨ÙØ¹ÙÙˆÙ’Ù„ÙØªÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ø§ÙÙˆÙ’ Ø§ÙØ®Ù’ÙˆÙØ§Ù†ÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ø§ÙÙˆÙ’ Ø¨ÙÙ†ÙÙŠÙ’Ù“ Ø§ÙØ®Ù’ÙˆÙØ§Ù†ÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ø§ÙÙˆÙ’ Ø¨ÙÙ†ÙÙŠÙ’Ù“ Ø§ÙØ®ÙÙˆÙ°ØªÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ø§ÙÙˆÙ’ Ù†ÙØ³ÙØ§Û¤Ù‰ÙÙ•Ù‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ø§ÙÙˆÙ’ Ù…ÙØ§ Ù…ÙÙ„ÙÙƒÙØªÙ’ Ø§ÙÙŠÙ’Ù…ÙØ§Ù†ÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ø§ÙÙˆÙ Ø§Ù„ØªÙ‘Ù°Ø¨ÙØ¹ÙÙŠÙ’Ù†Ù ØºÙÙŠÙ’Ø±Ù Ø§ÙÙˆÙ„ÙÙ‰ Ø§Ù„Ù’Ø§ÙØ±Ù’Ø¨ÙØ©Ù Ù…ÙÙ†Ù Ø§Ù„Ø±ÙÙ‘Ø¬ÙØ§Ù„Ù Ø§ÙÙˆÙ Ø§Ù„Ø·ÙÙ‘ÙÙ’Ù„Ù Ø§Ù„ÙÙ‘Ø°ÙÙŠÙ’Ù†Ù Ù„ÙÙ…Ù’ ÙŠÙØ¸Ù’Ù‡ÙØ±ÙÙˆÙ’Ø§ Ø¹ÙÙ„Ù°Ù‰ Ø¹ÙÙˆÙ’Ø±Ù°ØªÙ Ø§Ù„Ù†ÙÙ‘Ø³ÙØ§Û¤Ø¡Ù Û–ÙˆÙÙ„ÙØ§ ÙŠÙØ¶Ù’Ø±ÙØ¨Ù’Ù†Ù Ø¨ÙØ§ÙØ±Ù’Ø¬ÙÙ„ÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘ Ù„ÙÙŠÙØ¹Ù’Ù„ÙÙ…Ù Ù…ÙØ§ ÙŠÙØ®Ù’ÙÙÙŠÙ’Ù†Ù Ù…ÙÙ†Ù’ Ø²ÙÙŠÙ’Ù†ÙØªÙÙ‡ÙÙ†ÙÙ‘Û— ÙˆÙØªÙÙˆÙ’Ø¨ÙÙˆÙ’Ù“Ø§ Ø§ÙÙ„ÙÙ‰ Ø§Ù„Ù„Ù‘Ù°Ù‡Ù Ø¬ÙÙ…ÙÙŠÙ’Ø¹Ù‹Ø§ Ø§ÙÙŠÙÙ‘Ù‡Ù Ø§Ù„Ù’Ù…ÙØ¤Ù’Ù…ÙÙ†ÙÙˆÙ’Ù†Ù Ù„ÙØ¹ÙÙ„ÙÙ‘ÙƒÙÙ…Ù’ ØªÙÙÙ’Ù„ÙØ­ÙÙˆÙ’Ù†Ù Artinya: Mengatakan kepada para perempuan yang beriman hendaklah mereka menjaga, memelihara kemaluannya, dan janganlah menampakkan perhiasannya (bagian tubuhnya), kecuali yang (biasa) terlihat. Hendaklah mereka menutupkan kain kerudung ke dadanya. Hendaklah pula mereka tidak menampakkan perhiasannya (auratnya), kecuali kepada suami mereka, ayah mereka, ayah suami mereka, putra-putra mereka, putra-putra suami mereka, saudara-saudara laki-laki mereka, putra-putra saudara laki-laki mereka, putra-putra saudara perempuan mereka, para perempuan (sesama muslim), hamba sahaya yang mereka miliki, para pelayan laki-laki (tua) yang tidak mempunyai keinginan (terhadap perempuan), atau anak-anak yang belum mengerti tentang aurat perempuan. Hendaklah diketahui pula mereka tidak mengentakkan kaki agar perhiasan yang mereka sembunyikan. Bertobatlah kamu semua kepada Allah, wahai orang-orang yang beriman, agar kamu beruntung.}
